Note:
Darwin x86_64 (macOS/Intel) System Call Definitions

Defines all system call numbers, platform metadata, and registration logic for
macOS/Darwin running on x86_64 (Intel) processors.

Darwin/XNU syscall numbers include a class prefix in the upper bits:
- Class 0 (Mach): 0x1000000
- Class 1 (Unix): 0x2000000
- Class 2 (Diagnostic): 0x3000000

All standard POSIX-like syscalls use the Unix class (0x2000000 prefix).
The constants below include the full number with the 0x2000000 prefix
already applied, as this is what must be loaded into RAX before the
syscall instruction.

Syscall convention:
- Syscall number in RAX (with 0x2000000 prefix for Unix class)
- Arguments in RDI, RSI, RDX, R10, R8, R9
- Return value in RAX
- Error signaled via carry flag (CF=1 means error, RAX contains errno)
- Invoked via: syscall instruction
- RCX and R11 are clobbered by the syscall instruction

Reference: XNU kernel bsd/kern/syscalls.master
           /usr/include/sys/syscall.h on macOS
:End Note

Import "compiler/backend/syscalls/platforms/platform_interface.runa" as PlatformInterface
Import "compiler/backend/syscalls/syscall_registry.runa" as SyscallRegistry
Import "compiler/backend/machine_code/common/machine_code_interface.runa" as MachineCode
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Darwin x86_64 Syscall Number Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Note: All numbers include the 0x2000000 (33554432) Unix class prefix
Note: Base number = 0x2000000 + syscall_number_from_syscalls.master
Note: Reference: XNU bsd/kern/syscalls.master

Note: 0x2000000 = 33554432

