Note: ============================================================================
Note: Platform Info Creation
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_darwin_x86_64_platform_info" returns Integer:
    Note: Creates and returns a PlatformInfo structure for Darwin x86_64 (macOS Intel)
    Let info be PlatformInterface.create_platform_info(PlatformInterface.PLATFORM_DARWIN_X86_64, MachineCode.TARGET_ARCH_X86_64, MachineCode.TARGET_OS_DARWIN, 8, PlatformInterface.ENDIAN_LITTLE)
    If info is 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    PlatformInterface.platform_info_set_name(info, "Darwin x86_64 (macOS Intel)")
    PlatformInterface.platform_info_set_abi(info, "System V AMD64 ABI (Darwin)")

    Return info
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Syscall Registration
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "register_darwin_x86_64_syscalls" that takes registry as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Registers all Darwin x86_64 syscall definitions with the given registry
    Note: Returns 1 on success, 0 on failure
    If registry is 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let platform_id be PlatformInterface.PLATFORM_DARWIN_X86_64

    Let platform_info be create_darwin_x86_64_platform_info()
    If platform_info is 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let reg_result be SyscallRegistry.registry_register_platform(registry, platform_id, platform_info)
    If reg_result is 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let convention be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_convention(platform_id)
    If convention is 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    SyscallRegistry.register_convention(registry, platform_id, convention)

    Note: --- File I/O Syscalls ---

